RustPythonKotlinSwiftJavaScript <p>Add the <code>nostr</code> dependency in your <code>Cargo.toml</code> file:</p> <pre><code>[dependencies]
nostr = "0.24"
</code></pre> <p>Alternatively, you can add it directly from <code>git</code> source:</p> <pre><code>[dependencies]
nostr = { git = "https://github.com/rust-nostr/nostr", tag = "v0.24.0" }
</code></pre> <p>Note</p> <p>To use a specific commit, use <code>rev</code> instead of <code>tag</code>.</p> <p>The <code>nostr-protocol</code> package is available on the public PyPI:</p> <pre><code>pip install nostr-protocol </code></pre> <p>To use the Kotlin language bindings for <code>nostr</code> in your Android project add the following to your gradle dependencies:</p> <pre><code>repositories {
mavenCentral()
}

dependencies { implementation("io.github.rust-nostr:nostr:&lt;version&gt;")
}
</code></pre> <pre><code>npm i @rust-nostr/nostr
</code></pre>

RustPythonKotlinSwift <p>Add the <code>nostr-sdk</code> dependency in your <code>Cargo.toml</code> file:</p> <pre><code>[dependencies]
nostr-sdk = "0.24"
</code></pre> <p>Alternatively, you can add it directly from <code>git</code> source:</p> <pre><code>[dependencies]
nostr-sdk = { git = "https://github.com/rust-nostr/nostr", tag = "v0.24.0" }
</code></pre> <p>Note</p> <p>To use a specific commit, use <code>rev</code> instead of <code>tag</code>.</p> <p>The <code>nostr-sdk</code> package is available on the public PyPI:</p> <pre><code>pip install nostr-sdk </code></pre> <p>To use the Kotlin language bindings for <code>nostr-sdk</code> in your Android project add the following to your gradle dependencies:</p> <pre><code>repositories {
mavenCentral()
}

dependencies { implementation("io.github.rust-nostr:nostr-sdk:&lt;version&gt;")
}
</code></pre>
